com.example.bettertrialbook.models

Class ExperimentInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.bettertrialbook.models.ExperimentInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable, java.lang.Comparable<ExperimentInfo>

    public class ExperimentInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<ExperimentInfo>, android.os.Parcelable
    The ExperimentInfo class contains important information about each experiment. The class implements Comparable to allow it to be compared to itself easily. It implements Parcelable so it can be passed through intents between activities.

      • ExperimentInfo

        public ExperimentInfo(java.lang.String description,
                      java.lang.String ownerId,
                      java.lang.String publishStatus,
                      java.lang.String activeStatus,
                      java.lang.String id,
                      java.lang.String trialType,
                      boolean geoLocationRequired,
                      int minTrials,
                      java.lang.String region)
        Creates an ExperimentInfo object with the following parameters
        Parameters:
        description - A description of the experiment
        ownerId - The id of the experiment's owner
        publishStatus - Either 'Published' or 'Unpublished'
        activeStatus - Either 'Active' or 'Ended'
        id - The unique id of the experiment
        trialType - The kind of trials required for the experiment (Binomial, Count-based, Measurement, Non-negative integer)
        geoLocationRequired - Whether or not geolocation is required for trials submitted to the experiment
        minTrials - The minimum number of trials required for the experiment
        region - The region the experiment is taking place in
